DataAnalytics:
    •   Identifying the problem which we are going to solve
    •   Designing Data requirements. What data we do need to have just to be able solve the problem
    •   Pre-processing data. Clean data, perform some sort of processing
    •   Performing Analytics over data. Analyzing the data using specific process
    •   Visualizing the data

Types of BigData analytics:
    • Descriptive analysis: what is happening now based on incoming data. What was happen
    • Predictive analysis:  what will may happen in the future.
      Example: get data from sensors and see if something can happen in the future
    • Prescriptive analysis: what action should be taken based on some algorithm output.
      So data went through the algorithms and provide possible outputs...
      Example: Google car. Get data from sensor and decide what next step should be,
      turn left or turn right ...
    • Diagnostic analytics. Why did it happen. Understand root cost of problem

